WEBVTT

00:06.424 --> 00:08.039
(ALARM RINGING)

00:30.281 --> 00:31.270
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

00:34.619 --> 00:35.825
Come on in.

00:37.288 --> 00:39.279
I'm not doing any more chemo.

00:46.631 --> 00:47.666
Good plan.

00:48.466 --> 00:50.127
You'll be dead
in five months.

00:53.137 --> 00:55.799
We went for a cure,
it didn't work.

00:56.224 --> 00:58.715
I've thought
about this a lot.

00:58.809 --> 01:00.970
Five more months on
this Earth is reasonable.

01:01.187 --> 01:05.647
A year in the hospital
in excruciating pain is

01:08.152 --> 01:09.312
not.

01:09.820 --> 01:11.776
With two weeks on,
two weeks off of chemo,

01:11.906 --> 01:13.897
you could have way
more than a year.

01:14.325 --> 01:16.407
Maybe two or three.

01:16.494 --> 01:17.483
House.

01:20.414 --> 01:21.403
I'm sorry.

01:27.755 --> 01:29.495
I'm not gonna
let you just die.

02:20.599 --> 02:21.930
Hey.

02:22.059 --> 02:23.515
You know, management
research shows that

02:23.602 --> 02:26.139
the best ideas come
from casual contact.

02:26.647 --> 02:30.105
So, one set of season tickets.

02:30.735 --> 02:31.895
I got the seat next to you.

02:34.071 --> 02:35.402
First game is October 8th.

02:35.990 --> 02:38.982
It's about one month
after Wilson's
expiration date.

02:39.452 --> 02:41.534
This isn't
an unstructured collaboration.

02:41.620 --> 02:43.326
You're trying to
be the new Wilson.

02:43.414 --> 02:45.996
I'm trying to show you
there are other
people who care about you.

02:46.584 --> 02:50.122
Relax. I'm probably
not gonna fall apart.

02:55.468 --> 03:00.337
...five, six, seven, eight.
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

03:00.431 --> 03:05.346
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.
Here we go.

03:05.436 --> 03:06.425
Cradle. One...

03:06.520 --> 03:09.933
HOUSE: Put down the pom-poms
and step away
from the computer.

03:10.274 --> 03:13.641
46-year-old
oncologist refuses treatment.

03:13.778 --> 03:15.734
JESSICA: Foreman already
gave us a case.

03:15.821 --> 03:17.152
Wants us to keep
things as normal

03:17.239 --> 03:19.981
as possible for as
long as possible.

03:20.826 --> 03:22.942
Wilson is dying,
Chase is gone,

03:23.037 --> 03:25.153
how close to normal
do you think we can come?

03:25.456 --> 03:27.321
19-year-old cheerleader,
admitted with

03:27.416 --> 03:29.281
massive
nosebleed and dizziness.

03:29.919 --> 03:34.253
Wow, cool,
I just completely forgot
that my best friend is dying.

03:35.132 --> 03:36.793
Wait, thatjust reminded me.

03:36.967 --> 03:38.377
Head CT is clean.

03:38.552 --> 03:41.134
How can we turn Wilson
from a terminal idiot

03:41.222 --> 03:43.713
into an interminable
pain in the ass?

03:43.849 --> 03:46.261
A mini-stroke could
explain our patient's

03:46.352 --> 03:47.762
neuro symptoms and
his butterfingers.

03:47.853 --> 03:49.184
But not his bloody nose.

03:49.313 --> 03:52.305
My best friend is
trying to kill himself.

03:52.650 --> 03:54.515
He just wants to die
with a little dignity.

03:54.985 --> 03:56.191
There's no such thing.

03:58.322 --> 04:00.483
JESSICA: It's not
your choice, House.

04:00.616 --> 04:03.323
Your only choice here
is between
acceptance and misery.

04:07.373 --> 04:10.661
It's a midline granuloma.
Get your patient a PET scan.

04:19.718 --> 04:23.336
No lesions along
the optic track...
You already covered that.

04:24.181 --> 04:26.342
Maybe we should
get someone else
to take this case.

04:26.684 --> 04:28.800
Why? Because someone
somewhere is dying?

04:30.604 --> 04:31.593
(ELECTRONIC BEEP)

04:31.981 --> 04:33.187
Oh, crap! Turn off the mic.

04:33.357 --> 04:34.563
It is off.

04:36.235 --> 04:40.069
Not according to his brain.
His temporal lobe
is completely lit up.

04:40.698 --> 04:44.691
Auditory portion.
He's hearing something.

04:59.884 --> 05:01.249
Foreman's trying to date me.

05:02.052 --> 05:03.553
I assume that's
because you called him.

05:04.054 --> 05:05.510
No, I...

05:06.098 --> 05:09.181
Did you put
something in my coffee?

05:09.268 --> 05:13.602
You know how you
can be there for me
five months from now?

05:13.731 --> 05:15.722
Don't be dead
five months from now.

05:29.622 --> 05:30.657
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

05:30.748 --> 05:31.737
Hey, Wilson...

05:34.543 --> 05:35.658
Seriously?

05:35.794 --> 05:36.954
Just a little picker-downer.

05:37.755 --> 05:40.371
I assume this
unwanted interruption
means you're looking for me

05:40.466 --> 05:41.831
to discuss
the latest development

05:41.926 --> 05:44.008
in a case I don't
want to discuss.

05:44.261 --> 05:45.762
TAUB: Our patient is
hearing voices.

05:45.888 --> 05:47.879
He denies it,
but the PET scan
says otherwise.

05:47.973 --> 05:51.010
He's at the right age
for the onset
of schizophrenia.

05:51.101 --> 05:53.308
Yeah. You really need me.

05:53.437 --> 05:55.894
Ultrasound his abdomen
to check for schizophrenia.

05:55.981 --> 05:59.189
We already ordered
a psych evaluation,
but drugs could also cause...

05:59.276 --> 06:00.982
Tox screen was clean.

06:01.111 --> 06:02.487
Ultrasound his dorm.

06:04.949 --> 06:05.938
(COUGHING)

06:06.075 --> 06:10.444
Whoa! You guys can'tjust
come busting in here
without a warrant.

06:11.163 --> 06:14.246
We're not cops.
We're your roommate's doctors.

06:17.294 --> 06:22.038
Any idea what flavor of
drugs would be making
your roommate sick?

06:22.132 --> 06:24.123
Objection. Entrapment.

06:25.844 --> 06:27.004
I'm pre-law.

06:29.098 --> 06:30.304
Derrick doesn't party.

06:33.143 --> 06:34.474
JESSICA: Look at this.

06:34.937 --> 06:37.053
Why would he have
a picture of a little boy?

06:37.147 --> 06:38.933
Maybe it's his
nephew or something?

06:39.149 --> 06:40.138
Hidden in his sock drawer?

06:40.859 --> 06:41.894
Whoa!

06:41.986 --> 06:43.317
Creepy.

06:51.870 --> 06:54.156
JESSICA: We need to talk
to Derrick about
some medical matters.

06:54.290 --> 06:55.996
Well, she's my girlfriend.
She can be here for that.

06:58.460 --> 06:59.449
(CLEARS THROAT)

07:00.379 --> 07:04.292
We found this
in your dorm room.

07:04.842 --> 07:06.173
Who is that?

07:07.344 --> 07:08.550
Nobody.

07:09.346 --> 07:11.837
JESSICA: Then why was it
hidden in a drawer?

07:14.351 --> 07:15.636
Derrick, what's
she talking about?

07:19.148 --> 07:20.729
It's my brother,
Christopher.

07:22.985 --> 07:24.850
You never told me
you had a brother.

07:24.987 --> 07:27.353
Well, he's been dead
almost 10 years, so...

07:30.701 --> 07:32.237
Is that the voice
you hear in your head?

07:38.042 --> 07:39.031
(SNORTS)

07:39.209 --> 07:40.198
Mmml

07:42.296 --> 07:43.285
(GROANING)

07:48.927 --> 07:50.667
And, lo, he is risen.

07:51.597 --> 07:53.883
So now my hair's
gonna fall out next week?

07:54.850 --> 07:58.058
No, all I did was
temporarily kill you.
How was it?

07:58.729 --> 08:01.687
Look, I wasn't dead.
I was unconscious.

08:01.774 --> 08:05.562
No dreams or thoughts.
You experience nothing.

08:06.528 --> 08:09.565
Now, imagine that
without the waking
up on the couch part.

08:09.740 --> 08:12.402
Just nothing,
times infinity.

08:13.243 --> 08:17.703
You didn'tjust
prove death is nothing.
You proved propofol is.

08:20.417 --> 08:22.578
You're saying the end
is not the end?

08:25.714 --> 08:28.922
I was expecting,
"Nothing is better
than something lousy,"

08:29.051 --> 08:31.292
but not, "The angels
are waiting for me."

08:31.595 --> 08:32.926
I'm not having
this conversation.

08:33.222 --> 08:35.338
Why? Because it
doesn't make sense?

08:35.724 --> 08:38.136
Because I'm not
gonna change your mind,
and I don't care.

08:38.268 --> 08:40.350
More importantly,
you're not gonna change mine.

08:40.437 --> 08:42.689
There is no heaven,
there is no hell,

08:42.773 --> 08:45.310
your soul is not gonna
float out of your body

08:45.442 --> 08:47.979
and join some great,
unifying energy force.

08:48.112 --> 08:49.943
The fact that you're dying
is not gonna change that.

08:50.072 --> 08:51.937
Please, just go.

08:53.617 --> 08:54.982
(SIGHS)

08:58.789 --> 08:59.778
House.

09:01.959 --> 09:07.499
I have spent the last 20 years
holding the hands of
people as they die.

09:07.631 --> 09:10.122
When I watch that
transformation...

09:12.636 --> 09:17.596
I'm sorry, I don't believe
that we're just
a bag of chemicals.

09:24.314 --> 09:25.303
(DOOR CLOSES)

09:30.988 --> 09:34.776
So are we gonna
talk about the patient,
or wait for House?

09:35.492 --> 09:36.607
Viral encephalitis.

09:36.827 --> 09:38.317
It's been going
on for 10 years.

09:39.830 --> 09:42.788
I'm gonna go in there
and invite him to participate.

09:42.958 --> 09:45.165
I think he'd
welcome the distraction.

09:47.755 --> 09:48.744
Come with me?

09:53.385 --> 09:54.374
VVhy?

09:55.429 --> 09:58.091
When was the last time
House listened to
anything we said

09:58.182 --> 09:59.342
about anything personal?

10:00.184 --> 10:03.802
Maybe you'll feel better,
but sometimes, the truth is,

10:04.521 --> 10:07.103
there's nothing anyone can do.

10:12.112 --> 10:13.693
Temporal lobe epilepsy.

10:14.031 --> 10:15.362
Causes voices, dizziness.

10:15.449 --> 10:17.690
Trauma from a seizure
would explain the nose bleed.

10:19.328 --> 10:21.159
You know about
all of my siblings,

10:21.288 --> 10:23.119
and cousins,
and aunts and uncles, and...

10:23.207 --> 10:24.287
You're overreacting.

10:24.374 --> 10:26.535
Because you
don't trust me enough
to tell me about...

10:26.668 --> 10:29.796
Sorry. It's time to
go down for your test.

10:31.507 --> 10:34.169
If you want to wait here,
it'll only take about an hour.

10:34.259 --> 10:35.669
No, she's leaving.

10:37.095 --> 10:40.258
Derrick, come on. I mean,
we should at least talk.

10:40.516 --> 10:42.507
No, I'd rather
you just leave.

10:43.894 --> 10:45.225
And you don't need
to come back.

10:57.783 --> 11:00.195
Time. Any odd
tastes or smells?

11:00.911 --> 11:02.276
No. Feel fine.

11:03.372 --> 11:04.908
Things looked
fine on my end, too.

11:09.753 --> 11:12.415
So you won't
admit to your doctors

11:12.506 --> 11:14.713
that you're hearing
your brother's voice,

11:14.800 --> 11:16.586
which is dangerous.

11:16.718 --> 11:19.255
And now, you lost
your girlfriend over it.

11:19.930 --> 11:20.885
Which is stupid.

11:20.973 --> 11:22.713
I assume there's
more to the story?

11:23.475 --> 11:24.806
That's how I was raised.

11:26.562 --> 11:27.597
Short story.
Yeah.

11:29.106 --> 11:31.222
My boss is losing his
best friend to cancer.

11:31.650 --> 11:34.141
And instead of
talking about the pain,

11:34.278 --> 11:36.519
he's pretending
there is no pain,

11:36.613 --> 11:38.478
because
everything can be fixed.

11:44.746 --> 11:46.122
My father tried
to deal with it.

11:47.583 --> 11:49.494
Ironic that he'd drink
himself into oblivion

11:49.585 --> 11:51.951
after my brother was
killed by a drunk driver.

11:57.134 --> 11:58.340
Do you need a tissue?

12:02.472 --> 12:06.886
After Dad left,
my mom moved us away.

12:06.977 --> 12:10.936
She got rid of all
the pictures of Christopher
and never mentioned him again.

12:11.315 --> 12:12.350
It was like he never existed.

12:13.483 --> 12:15.064
And that worked for us.

12:15.152 --> 12:16.767
And, yet, you kept one.

12:19.072 --> 12:20.858
Uh... My right eye...

12:21.450 --> 12:24.658
I was seeing spots,
but now I can't see at all.
Is that from the test?

12:25.871 --> 12:27.156
No, this is something else.

