12:50.687 --> 12:51.676
Hey.

12:52.481 --> 12:53.516
Saved us a table.

12:53.649 --> 12:54.638
There are notables.

12:54.733 --> 12:57.816
I recently hacked
into your old files.

12:57.903 --> 13:01.111
Found a 6-year-old boy
with bilateral retinoblastoma.

13:01.198 --> 13:02.654
Doctors wanted to
take his eyes out

13:02.783 --> 13:04.193
before the cancer
spread to his brain.

13:04.326 --> 13:09.946
But you fought them.
Advocated for a new
photon beam radiation.

13:10.040 --> 13:12.406
Saved the kid's vision,
probably saved his life.

13:12.876 --> 13:16.494
That was my
first case at PPTH.
Mikey Kimble.

13:16.588 --> 13:17.748
It's Michael, now.

13:20.425 --> 13:22.916
Oh, yeah, this is our table.

13:23.053 --> 13:24.088
Wow.

13:25.222 --> 13:26.211
(STAMMERING)

13:29.810 --> 13:30.799
How are you?

13:30.894 --> 13:34.136
I'm doing great.
Graduating next month.

13:34.481 --> 13:37.644
Already? Little Mikey?

13:38.443 --> 13:40.695
And I got
accepted to Princeton.

13:40.821 --> 13:43.062
I'm planning on
going to med school.

13:43.407 --> 13:44.396
(CHUCKLES)

13:44.992 --> 13:47.904
He's going to be a doctor.
Instead of being dead.

13:50.414 --> 13:54.908
Dr. House told me all
about your situation.

13:55.127 --> 13:56.867
That's why I came.

13:56.962 --> 13:59.078
There's just so much
good that you can do,

13:59.214 --> 14:01.330
even in a small
amount of time.

14:05.137 --> 14:06.422
I wonder...

14:08.765 --> 14:09.754
Hey!

14:09.933 --> 14:14.267
Is there anybody else
here who's alive today
because of Dr. James Wilson?

14:34.291 --> 14:39.035
Gastric adenocarcinoma.
Fifteen years in remission.

14:39.296 --> 14:42.880
Six grandchildren
that I never would have met.

14:43.133 --> 14:44.543
Thank you, Dr. Wilson.

14:46.511 --> 14:47.796
Squamous cell lung cancer.

14:47.888 --> 14:50.049
Twelve years in remission.

14:50.140 --> 14:52.472
I was able to walk my daughter
down the aisle last May.

14:53.852 --> 14:54.841
Thank you, Dr. Wilson.

15:05.781 --> 15:06.770
HOUSE: I did the math.

15:07.699 --> 15:10.941
Seventy-four
children are alive today
because of you.

15:12.329 --> 15:14.160
Fourteen grandchildren.

15:18.043 --> 15:21.456
Mikey Kimble
started kindergarten
before the age cut-off.

15:24.049 --> 15:26.131
He would have graduated
high school last year.

15:29.471 --> 15:30.460
I flunked a year?

15:32.724 --> 15:35.215
Was anybody in this room
really a patient of mine?

15:42.442 --> 15:43.431
They're somewhere.

15:44.194 --> 15:45.934
They're giving you
a standing "0" somewhere.

15:47.197 --> 15:49.313
They exist.
You saved their lives.

15:50.951 --> 15:53.818
It's actually more impressive
that they're too
busy to be here.

15:59.668 --> 16:00.657
What's this?

16:00.752 --> 16:02.162
A glowing letter
of recommendation

16:02.254 --> 16:04.336
you just wrote
for me on my laptop.

16:04.422 --> 16:06.708
I noticed it's lacking
your signature at the bottom.

16:06.842 --> 16:09.834
Don't you think you're
being a bit premature
predicting House's demise?

16:09.928 --> 16:12.010
Not demise, just implosion.

16:13.348 --> 16:14.929
He's going
through a rough time.

16:15.058 --> 16:16.889
But, so far,
he's been handling it...
(SLOSHING)

16:28.530 --> 16:29.519
House?

16:32.200 --> 16:33.656
Your shoes are wet.

16:33.743 --> 16:35.449
Glad to see your
emotional turmoil

16:35.537 --> 16:37.903
hasn't dulled your
powers of observation.

16:38.665 --> 16:40.280
I know you're responsible.

16:40.375 --> 16:44.960
No, you don't.
Because I didn't do it.
Whatever "it" is.

16:45.922 --> 16:48.538
But if I had shoved
those season tickets
down some toilets,

16:48.633 --> 16:50.589
I would have done it
because you asked me to.

16:51.803 --> 16:55.091
You wanted to replace Wilson.
I prank Wilson all the time.

16:55.182 --> 16:56.467
Enjoy.

17:09.946 --> 17:10.935
(BELL CHIMING)

17:19.789 --> 17:22.576
I got you three,
but I drank them.

17:25.503 --> 17:28.916
You didn't have to call me,
but I appreciate
I made the list.

17:29.466 --> 17:31.252
It wasn't entirely unselfish.

17:38.433 --> 17:40.389
I didn't feel
right approaching

17:40.477 --> 17:42.889
any of my
terminal patients, but...

17:49.236 --> 17:50.442
What is it like?

17:51.655 --> 17:52.644
Hmm...

17:53.573 --> 17:56.064
Does it ever
stop being surreal?

17:58.787 --> 18:04.373
It'll stop in about
five or six months,
give or take, in your case.

18:05.627 --> 18:06.616
(CHUCKLES)

18:07.337 --> 18:09.874
You know what
happened to me today?

18:09.965 --> 18:13.298
One of my patients
suddenly started crying.

18:14.010 --> 18:15.341
It can't be your first.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.881
It was the first one
who was crying for me.

18:21.893 --> 18:25.636
It's the human response.
It's either overly saccharine,

18:25.730 --> 18:27.891
because giving sympathy
makes them feel better,

18:28.108 --> 18:29.439
or they ignore you,

18:29.526 --> 18:32.484
because hiding from mortality
makes them feel better.

18:33.071 --> 18:35.904
Well, why can't
they just say something
that makes me feel better?

18:36.866 --> 18:38.197
Like what, exactly?

18:41.037 --> 18:42.026
(LAUGHING)

18:43.707 --> 18:45.322
I don't know.
No.

18:46.126 --> 18:47.115
Mmm...

18:50.130 --> 18:52.496
You'd be doing what?
Two weeks on, two weeks off?

18:53.633 --> 18:55.544
So maybe do your first round,
see how it goes.

18:56.219 --> 18:58.460
May be not as
horrible as you fear.

18:58.555 --> 19:00.887
Then do the second round,
enjoy your two weeks off,

19:00.974 --> 19:04.717
and revisit the decision.
Rinse, repeat.

19:09.274 --> 19:12.641
I just can't envision
spending my remaining time

19:12.736 --> 19:14.943
in a chemo suite
in Princeton.

19:19.284 --> 19:23.698
I want to enjoy myself
with family and friends.

19:26.124 --> 19:28.410
Friends, or friend?

19:31.129 --> 19:33.871
Hi, this is Greg House again.
Third message.

19:33.965 --> 19:37.207
Hopefully indicating
how much I want
you to call me back.

19:37.302 --> 19:40.294
I'd say that your son is dying
to increase the urgency,

19:40.388 --> 19:42.219
but you probably
already know that.

19:43.767 --> 19:46.634
The fake people who care
that Wilson stays
alive didn't work,

19:46.728 --> 19:48.639
so I need the real people
who care about him

19:48.730 --> 19:50.311
to tell him what
an idiot he's being.

19:50.607 --> 19:51.687
Where are we going?

19:51.858 --> 19:53.394
Well, ljust got paged
to go to the bathroom.

19:53.526 --> 19:55.062
I don't know where
the rest of you are going.

19:55.987 --> 19:58.194
Some of our
patient's symptoms
might be physiological

20:00.116 --> 20:01.947
You think being forced
to bury painful memories

20:02.035 --> 20:03.150
is making his symptoms worse?

20:03.244 --> 20:06.077
Grief avoidance can lead
to all sorts of
anxiety disorders,

20:06.164 --> 20:09.998
which can manifest
into physical illness.

20:10.877 --> 20:14.916
Let's assume that
all his symptoms
are real symptoms.

20:15.799 --> 20:18.506
So we're going to
avoid grief avoidance?

20:18.635 --> 20:20.296
Studies after
September 11th showed that

20:20.428 --> 20:22.134
repression was
actually better for coping

20:22.222 --> 20:23.428
than dwelling in misery.

20:23.765 --> 20:25.050
What about polycythemia vera?

20:25.141 --> 20:27.257
JESSICA: RBC's are slightly
elevated, but not that much.

20:27.394 --> 20:28.804
Hodgkin's lymphoma?

20:28.937 --> 20:30.302
Would have shown
up on the PET scan.

20:30.897 --> 20:32.762
What if our guy
got hurt at practice

20:33.316 --> 20:35.648
and, like everything else,
just didn't tell anyone?

20:35.985 --> 20:37.896
Could have set off DIC.
Would explain everything.

20:38.988 --> 20:40.489
I thought you had to
go to the bathroom.

20:40.949 --> 20:42.155
I didn't say I had to go in.

20:43.660 --> 20:45.150
Need some more mops in here!

20:50.500 --> 20:52.411
What exactly are
you looking for?

20:52.919 --> 20:56.411
Blood. If your
spinal fluid is yellow
instead of clear,

20:56.506 --> 20:58.246
it means you've had
a subarachnoid hemorrhage.

21:01.511 --> 21:03.968
What does your
brother say to you?

21:04.180 --> 21:06.762
Does he tell you
you're gonna be okay?

21:08.143 --> 21:10.179
ItdoesnT
really work like that.

21:11.438 --> 21:14.350
I think you hear
your brother's voice
for a reason.

21:14.607 --> 21:17.098
I thought you guys
said that I hear things
because I'm sick.

21:17.193 --> 21:20.105
Yes, but that doesn't explain
why you don't hear
a different voice.

21:20.447 --> 21:22.563
I think your mom
didn't let you deal

21:22.699 --> 21:24.860
with the grief of
losing your brother properly.

21:26.369 --> 21:29.202
There are people here
who could help you with that.

21:33.877 --> 21:34.866
Okay.

21:41.134 --> 21:42.670
The opening
pressure's way too high.

22:03.740 --> 22:05.696
The prodigal daughter returns.

22:07.702 --> 22:09.863
You taking me up on
my offer to off you?

22:10.079 --> 22:12.331
I think I've still got
some leftover propofol.

22:12.499 --> 22:13.909
I spoke to Wilson.

22:15.543 --> 22:19.912
He's angry because I
want him to live longer.
Who wouldn't be?

22:20.673 --> 22:22.083
Friends respect
each other's decisions,

22:22.258 --> 22:23.668
evenifthey
don't agree with them.

22:23.760 --> 22:24.749
It's called loyalty.

22:24.844 --> 22:26.550
LoyaHyis
a tool to get people

22:26.679 --> 22:28.260
to do things they
don't want to do.

22:30.183 --> 22:31.172
But you do want to.

22:33.269 --> 22:36.261
And you may have
rationalized it
100 different ways,

22:36.356 --> 22:38.438
but the fact is
you fired me so that

22:38.608 --> 22:40.690
I'd be forced to
spend the rest of my life

22:40.777 --> 22:43.268
doing exactly
what I wanted to do.

22:52.789 --> 22:53.869
And you don't even
like me that much.

23:04.968 --> 23:05.957
(DOOR OPENS)

23:07.929 --> 23:08.918
HOUSE: I surrender.

23:17.730 --> 23:20.597
I have been a disloyal,

23:20.984 --> 23:21.973
(DOOR CLOSES)

23:22.485 --> 23:23.986
disrespectful jerk.

23:25.613 --> 23:27.149
I should've listened
to what you wanted.

23:28.449 --> 23:30.940
I'm still not
letting my parents
return your call.

23:31.327 --> 23:35.070
I made a reservation
for two at Carmine's.
Tonight, 8:00.

23:36.583 --> 23:39.666
No more tricks.
No more manipulations.

23:40.128 --> 23:41.493
Said Machiavelli.

23:42.005 --> 23:47.341
Just two friends enjoying
the time they have left.

23:47.635 --> 23:49.011
Please, don't...
I'm not.

23:49.637 --> 23:50.626
I promise.

23:53.850 --> 23:54.839
Just dinner?

23:55.602 --> 23:57.467
That depends on
how much you have to drink.

24:00.690 --> 24:02.180
Sounds nice.

24:12.160 --> 24:13.115
Mom.

24:13.202 --> 24:14.282
I came as soon as
I got your message.

24:14.370 --> 24:15.325
Is he gonna be okay?

24:15.413 --> 24:17.449
We're hoping it's
just excess fluid

24:17.540 --> 24:19.576
on his brain from
an extreme migraine.

24:20.043 --> 24:22.079
Which isn't good,
but it's treatable.

24:22.545 --> 24:25.662
He's scheduled to get an MRI
as soon as these meds
start taking effect.

24:32.013 --> 24:34.049
We found that
picture in his dorm room.

24:35.642 --> 24:38.850
I'm not sure what
Derrick's told you,

24:40.521 --> 24:43.888
but he's been
hearing Christopher's voice
for the last 10 years.

24:44.275 --> 24:48.109
And it's possible that
repressing all
that grief he's felt

24:48.196 --> 24:50.858
is actually causing some of
Derrick's symptoms.

24:54.202 --> 24:57.319
I don't even know if
this voice in my head
is something I invented,

24:57.413 --> 24:59.369
or if it's what
Christopher was really like.

25:00.124 --> 25:02.206
With no photos, no video,

25:03.753 --> 25:05.209
my memories,

25:07.131 --> 25:09.918
I really don't
have any anymore.

25:12.178 --> 25:13.839
Maybe you could just

25:17.016 --> 25:19.473
tell me
a little bit about him?

25:23.398 --> 25:25.514
I'm sorry.
It was a long drive in.

25:27.068 --> 25:28.433
I'm gonna go get a coffee.

25:30.530 --> 25:31.519
Okay.

25:39.497 --> 25:43.206
Seventy-nine years old
and you told her
she was pregnant.

25:43.626 --> 25:45.742
(CHUCKLING)
Well, it cured
her hiccups.

25:46.045 --> 25:47.751
(WILSON LAUGHING)

25:47.964 --> 25:51.252
I'll say I didn't
expect her to cry
for quite so long.

25:52.802 --> 25:55.509
Now, I know that
the tiramisu is great here,

25:55.638 --> 25:58.380
but I actually
ordered off menu.

26:07.275 --> 26:11.439
Greg,
I told you you didn't hang
the bear bag high enough.

26:12.071 --> 26:13.356
It was a smart bear.

26:13.614 --> 26:15.354
I'm almost certain
he untied my knots.

26:15.533 --> 26:17.740
Well, he wasn't that smart.
He left the Oreos behind.

26:17.910 --> 26:23.121
You hiked for 32 miles
eating nothing
but creamy filling.

26:23.750 --> 26:25.331
The black stuff is overrated.

26:27.295 --> 26:28.785
To climbing the hill.

26:35.970 --> 26:38.052
Okay.

26:38.139 --> 26:43.099
If I did decide to stick
around a little longer...

26:43.186 --> 26:44.551
Don't do that to me, Wilson.

26:44.687 --> 26:47.645
No, I'm not. I'm just...

26:47.732 --> 26:52.192
I do feel pretty good,
and maybe I should try it.

26:53.404 --> 26:54.689
For a little while.

26:59.202 --> 27:00.863
I think that's reasonable.

27:12.298 --> 27:13.413
Are you conning me?

27:17.845 --> 27:18.834
You're conning me.

27:19.222 --> 27:20.211
What?

27:20.723 --> 27:24.807
Just because you folded,
that means it must
be some evil plan?

27:25.186 --> 27:29.976
Well, that's usually
how it works with you.
You drown me in nostalgia,

27:30.066 --> 27:32.899
so I'll think
about our friendship
and feel some kind of loyalty,

27:32.985 --> 27:35.237
and agree to more chemo.

27:35.321 --> 27:38.188
That was real nostalgia,
it was real emotion,
it's a real decision.

27:38.282 --> 27:40.944
A decision that I
just made for you.

27:51.963 --> 27:53.828
I want you to be
around as long as possible,

27:55.550 --> 27:57.415
because I don't know
what I'm gonna do without you.

27:57.510 --> 27:59.876
No! No. Don't do that.

28:01.055 --> 28:03.546
I don't owe you anything.

28:03.641 --> 28:05.927
Our entire relationship
has been about you.

28:07.061 --> 28:09.017
My dying is about me.

28:25.204 --> 28:27.616
(SOBBING)

28:32.503 --> 28:33.492
(SIGHING)

28:42.972 --> 28:43.961
(SNIFFLING)

28:59.280 --> 29:01.145
Look at you.
You don't wanna die.

29:01.490 --> 29:02.991
Of course,
I don't wanna die.

29:03.117 --> 29:04.653
Then fight.

29:04.744 --> 29:06.359
I did. I tried.

29:06.537 --> 29:07.617
One time.

29:07.705 --> 29:09.070
House, get out of my car.

29:09.248 --> 29:10.749
You don't have to
just accept this.

29:10.833 --> 29:14.121
Yes, I do have to accept this.
I have five months to live.

29:14.253 --> 29:16.710
And you're making me
go through this alone?

29:22.887 --> 29:27.221
I'm pissed because I'm dying.
That's not fair.

29:27.308 --> 29:28.297
And I need...

29:31.228 --> 29:32.217
I need a friend.

29:32.688 --> 29:35.100
I need to know that
you're there. I need...

29:38.361 --> 29:42.650
I need you to tell me
that my life was worthwhile.

29:43.366 --> 29:48.656
And I need you to
tell me that you love me.

29:59.423 --> 30:00.412
No.

30:01.717 --> 30:03.969
I'm not gonna tell you
that unless you fight.

30:18.442 --> 30:21.934
Blood vessels
are non-reactive.
It's not a migraine.

30:22.029 --> 30:25.021
I’m not feeling so great,
how much longer?

30:25.574 --> 30:26.654
Finishing up.

30:26.742 --> 30:27.731
(ELECTRONIC BEEPING)

30:33.582 --> 30:34.617
Thank you, Dr. Adams.

30:38.170 --> 30:39.159
(RUMBLING)

30:39.922 --> 30:41.287
It looks like
the ceiling might...

30:54.687 --> 30:55.676
(SIRENS WAILING)

30:55.938 --> 30:57.394
(CHATTER OVER POLICE RADIO)

31:22.423 --> 31:23.629
What are you doing back here?

31:23.716 --> 31:27.459
We got a case.
I assume the status is
patient's getting worse,

31:27.553 --> 31:28.963
you guys are confused.

31:29.722 --> 31:31.929
You think actually
showing up for work

31:32.058 --> 31:34.265
is enough to make up
for ruining an MRI?

31:34.393 --> 31:36.805
Endangering the patient,
injuring us?

31:36.896 --> 31:38.978
I've got an airtight
alibi that I'm working on.

31:39.065 --> 31:40.475
This isn't about the damage.
You're back

31:40.608 --> 31:42.018
because something's
going on with Wilson.

31:42.193 --> 31:43.433
I'm done with Wilson.

31:43.694 --> 31:45.309
What does that mean,
you're done with Wilson?

31:45.404 --> 31:47.520
If he's not dead,
you're not done with Wilson.

31:47.615 --> 31:49.151
Suddenly, you think
you're gonna
make a difference?

31:49.575 --> 31:50.815
You can'tjust abandon him.

31:50.993 --> 31:53.029
It's in his hands now.
Did you get

31:53.162 --> 31:55.198
any good pictures
before the MRI drowned?

31:55.331 --> 31:57.572
Enough to know it
wasn't a migraine.

31:57.708 --> 31:59.949
And the patient
mistook me for Adams.

32:09.553 --> 32:10.804
Come with me.

32:15.142 --> 32:17.303
Hey.

32:17.394 --> 32:18.520
So what do you
think's gonna happen

32:18.604 --> 32:20.265
when I stick
a needle into his eardrum?

32:20.356 --> 32:21.562
You quizzing us?

32:21.649 --> 32:23.014
This is a good quiz.

32:23.192 --> 32:24.557
He'll scream in pain.

32:24.652 --> 32:25.687
HOUSE: Don't listen to her.

32:25.778 --> 32:27.518
Very small needle,
very steady hands.

32:29.198 --> 32:30.529
Now, when I pull
back on the plunger,

32:30.658 --> 32:31.989
what do you think
is gonna come out?

32:32.159 --> 32:33.148
Air.

32:39.625 --> 32:41.286
Boy, that air sure is red.

32:42.336 --> 32:44.327
Persistent Stapedial Artery.

32:44.421 --> 32:46.503
It should disappear
in the embryonic stage.

32:46.632 --> 32:49.544
But just like
his dead brother,
he really can't let go.

32:49.635 --> 32:52.422
So the artery's been pressing
against the temporal
lobe of his brain,

32:52.513 --> 32:53.548
right above the ear canal.

32:53.639 --> 32:55.800
Explains the voices,
the dizziness, everything.

32:57.017 --> 32:59.053
Now you guys can explain
how we're gonna
make him better.

33:05.609 --> 33:07.145
Will my brother's
voice go away?

33:14.660 --> 33:15.945
You're being an ass.

33:16.871 --> 33:18.827
ljust cured a patient.
How about you?

33:18.914 --> 33:20.324
You can'tjust
give up on Wilson.

33:20.916 --> 33:22.076
You know he needs you.

33:22.376 --> 33:23.741
You know he's making
an impossible choice.

33:23.878 --> 33:25.243
He just doesn't
want to live in pain.

33:25.754 --> 33:27.005
Life is pain.

33:27.339 --> 33:30.672
Iwake up every
morning and I'm in pain.
I go to work in pain.

33:30.759 --> 33:32.590
You know how many times
I've wanted to just give up?

33:33.137 --> 33:34.752
How many times
I've thought about ending it?

33:56.285 --> 33:57.274
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

34:01.373 --> 34:04.160
You here to yell at me,
or give me hockey tickets?

34:04.251 --> 34:05.866
Had to delay the surgery
because our patient

34:06.003 --> 34:07.664
drank ammonia from
the janitor's cart.

34:09.048 --> 34:12.211
I guess he didn't want to live
without his brother's voice.

34:18.015 --> 34:19.346
Where are you going?

34:26.690 --> 34:28.396
You can't wait to die?

34:29.276 --> 34:30.265
Here, let me help you.

34:30.361 --> 34:31.851
Hey!Hey!
House!

34:31.987 --> 34:32.976
House!

34:33.530 --> 34:35.031
See? You wanna live.

34:35.157 --> 34:37.068
He did something stupid.
He's not gonna do it again.

34:37.159 --> 34:40.947
You're resisting me
because it's our human
responsibility to stay alive!

34:41.038 --> 34:43.575
You've made your point, House!
Stop!

34:50.798 --> 34:51.787
(GASPING)

34:56.345 --> 34:59.212
You've spent your whole life
looking for the truth.

34:59.306 --> 35:02.093
Well, sometimes,
the truth just sucks.

35:08.440 --> 35:09.429
Um, um...

35:11.694 --> 35:16.609
I'm going to be leaving, uh...
Quite a bit earlier
than we had talked about.

35:19.410 --> 35:20.775
Next day or two.

35:22.538 --> 35:24.745
What happened?

35:24.832 --> 35:26.413
Something
between you and House?

35:30.296 --> 35:31.456
He's not my child.

35:33.173 --> 35:37.837
I cannot be responsible
for the happiness
of Gregory House.

35:40.681 --> 35:42.797
(STAMMERING) I'll give
these to Frankel.

35:43.142 --> 35:44.131
Okay, thank you.

35:46.937 --> 35:49.519
And you are responsible.

35:53.193 --> 35:57.812
The past 20 years,
you've had three wives,

35:58.907 --> 36:01.740
hundreds of colleagues,
thousands of patients.

36:03.579 --> 36:05.490
But you've kept
that one best friend.

36:07.708 --> 36:12.042
He wants me to suffer
a misery that I don't
want to go through.

36:16.592 --> 36:18.674
Chemo won't make
your life any better.

36:19.762 --> 36:20.968
But caring will.

36:22.056 --> 36:25.344
Enduring pain to do some good
for someone you care about.

36:26.226 --> 36:27.602
Isn't that What life is?

37:06.809 --> 37:08.640
(SOMBER PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

37:41.885 --> 37:42.874
Mom.

37:46.014 --> 37:47.003
Yeah?

37:48.016 --> 37:50.598
That picture of Christopher
that I had on the stand,

37:52.729 --> 37:53.809
did you take it?

37:56.608 --> 37:57.597
Yes.

37:59.027 --> 38:00.312
Did you throw it out?

38:05.117 --> 38:06.948
If I agree to
get this surgery,

38:07.077 --> 38:08.908
can you bring
that picture back?

38:39.985 --> 38:40.974
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

38:43.447 --> 38:45.278
Not home.
WILSON: House.

38:51.955 --> 38:53.946
I'm ready to start
the next round of chemo.

38:56.293 --> 38:57.328
VVhy?

38:58.670 --> 39:00.046
Because you need me.

39:00.756 --> 39:05.090
And I don't think
that's a bad thing anymore.

39:08.555 --> 39:09.544
No.

39:11.975 --> 39:14.762
You're the only
one I listen to.

39:14.853 --> 39:18.016
And the last couple
of days, I didn't.
I almost killed my patient.

39:18.732 --> 39:20.643
So I think it's
time for me to accept

39:20.734 --> 39:25.444
that you're just
smarter than I am.

39:29.451 --> 39:32.238
Are you really okay that
there's only five months left?

39:34.122 --> 39:35.111
No.

39:37.417 --> 39:38.702
But it's better than nothing.

39:43.048 --> 39:44.037
Um...

39:45.634 --> 39:46.749
How do we start?

39:50.389 --> 39:51.595
Well, I'm not gonna say,
"I love you."

39:52.432 --> 39:54.423
Thank God. Got any Oreos?

39:58.021 --> 39:59.352
(FOLK MUSIC PLAYING)

40:10.242 --> 40:13.200
Hey. How you feeling?

40:19.167 --> 40:20.543
The surgery worked.

40:21.920 --> 40:22.909
How can you tell?

40:24.464 --> 40:25.920
Because Christopher's gone.

41:31.615 --> 41:34.357
And this is the peak.
Almost 8,000 feet.

41:35.077 --> 41:39.286
You do realize
that my leg situation
has deteriorated a little

41:39.373 --> 41:40.829
since the last
time we went hiking.

41:40.916 --> 41:42.326
So add another day.

41:42.417 --> 41:43.406
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

41:43.502 --> 41:44.491
(DOOR OPENS)

41:46.963 --> 41:49.750
This is Matt Johnson,
the hospital lawyer.

41:53.637 --> 41:55.468
Yes, I have decided
not to proceed

41:55.597 --> 41:57.462
with the sexual
harassment case.

41:58.100 --> 41:59.089
Are these yours?

42:00.936 --> 42:04.224
The plumber
retrieved them from
the hospital outflow pipe.

42:04.314 --> 42:07.556
They caused the sewage back up
that ruined the MRI.

42:07.651 --> 42:09.016
And they have
your name on them.

42:10.112 --> 42:13.980
Gregory Danger House?
It's a very common name.

42:14.074 --> 42:16.690
These apparently
have your finger
prints on them also.

42:19.996 --> 42:21.827
Okay, well, why don't you
tell me how many hours

42:21.915 --> 42:23.746
of picking up trash
you want me to do?

42:23.959 --> 42:26.621
House, I tried to
keep this internal.

42:27.963 --> 42:30.204
The fire department
handed the tickets
to the police,

42:31.550 --> 42:33.086
who contacted
your parole officer.

42:33.760 --> 42:35.091
It's felony vandalism.

42:36.054 --> 42:37.760
He's gonna revoke your parole.

42:38.682 --> 42:39.842
There's nothing we can do.

42:39.975 --> 42:41.806
You have to report
to Mercer County Jail
on Monday

42:41.893 --> 42:43.724
to serve out
the rest of your sentence.

42:50.861 --> 42:53.728
And that's how long?

42:55.157 --> 42:57.068
I'm sorry.
How long?

43:05.125 --> 43:06.410
Six months.
